# Dairo + Flask

This starter was scaffolded by `dairo init flask`. It is a Flask app with an
outbound send route and an inbound webhook handler that verifies delivery
signatures.

## Files

- `app.py` — the Flask app: `POST /api/dairo/send` and the inbound webhook
  handler at `POST {{inbox_route}}`.

## 1. Set your API key

```sh
cp .env.example .env
```

```text
DAIRO_API_KEY=dairo_...
DAIRO_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
```

`Dairo()` reads `DAIRO_API_KEY` from the environment.

## 2. Install and run

```sh
{{install_cmd}}
flask --app app run --port 5000
```

## 3. Register the webhook

```sh
dairo webhook create --url https://<your-tunnel>{{inbox_route}} --event {{webhook_event}}
```

Local development:

```sh
dairo listen --forward-to http://localhost:5000{{inbox_route}}
```

## Raw body gotcha

`request.get_data()` returns the **raw bytes**. Dairo signs over those bytes, so
verify before `json.loads`. Do not use `request.get_json()` for the webhook body
— verify the raw bytes first.
